                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="rubrication" xml:id="d0">Nomina sacra name of the protagonist of Text II, name of the donors and his family members; elements of the punctuation signs, of the text dividers and of the quire marks; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
Several groups of lines on the incipit pages of Texts I-1 and II, alternating with black lines; initial two lines of each section of Text I, II, V, VI, and of each miracle of Texts III and IV; the words salām “salutation” and sǝbḥat “glory” in Text VI; first word of each stanza in Text VI.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">- f. 3r (incipit page of Text I-1): coloured (strong red, black) ornamental band; geometric motifs.</decoNote>
